This is "savetape" a project from the Lazaret archaeological laboratory.

Savetape is a  Python script and a Module used to regulary save directories on an unix tape.

You can see the last news about this project at our Trac page :
http://lazaret.unice.fr/opensource/


-----
to change default saved directories option modify the files :
/use/local/bin/savetotape.sh


-----
Command line usage
| savetotape.sh [options]

Actualy only a few options :

-v or --verbose : Verbose mode
-h or --help : Short help on usage
--version : version of the script

Example :
| savetotape.sh -v